<page>
<title>True / False</title>
<problem>
    <introduction>
        <p>
            (8 points) Suppose <m>A</m> is an <m>m \times n</m> matrix and <m>\vec b\in \mathbb R ^{m}</m> unless otherwise stated. Select <em>true</em> if the statement is true for all choices of <m>A</m> and <m>\vec b</m>.  Otherwise, select <em>false</em>.
        </p>
    </introduction>
    <task workspace="true">
    <statement>
        <p>
            <em>True &#160;  / &#160;  False</em>: &#160; If <m>A</m> and <m>B</m> are row equivalent, then <m>\det (A) = \det (B)</m>.
        </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
            False.
        </p>
    </answer>
    <solution>
        <p>
            Solution text
        </p>
        <p>
            Counterexample: 
        </p>
    </solution>
    </task>

    <task workspace="true">
        <statement>
            <p>
                <em>True &#160;  / &#160;  False</em>: &#160; If <m>\vec{p}</m> and <m> \vec{q} </m> are probability vectors in <m>\mathbb R ^3</m>, then <m>\frac{1}{3} \vec{p}  + \frac{2}{3} \vec{q}</m> is also a probability vector in <m>\mathbb R ^3</m>.
            </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
            <p>
                True.
            </p>
        </answer>
        <solution>
            <p>
                Solution text
            </p>    
        </solution>
    </task>

    <task workspace="true">
        <statement>
            <p>
                <em>True &#160;  / &#160;  False</em>: &#160; If the matrix product <m> AB </m> is defined, then the product <m>BA</m> is also defined.
            </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
            <p>
                False
            </p>
        </answer>
        <solution>
            <p>
                Solution text
            </p>
        </solution>
    </task>

    <task workspace="true">
        <statement>
            <p>
                <em>True &#160;  / &#160;  False</em>: &#160; If <m>\det (A) = 0</m>, then <m>A</m> must have a zero row or have two rows which are identical.
            </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
            <p>
                False
            </p>
        </answer>
        <solution>
            <p>
                Solution text
            </p>
        </solution>
    </task>

    <task workspace="true">
        <statement>
            <p>
                <em>True &#160;  / &#160;  False</em>: &#160; If <m>A</m> is an <m>n \times n</m> matrix and <m>A = LU</m> is an <m>LU</m> factorization of <m>A</m>, then <m>\det(A) = \det(U)</m>.
            </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
            <p>
                True
            </p>
        </answer>
        <solution>
            <p>
                Solution text
            </p>
        </solution>
    </task>

    <task workspace="true">
        <statement>
            <p>
                <em>True &#160;  / &#160;  False</em>: &#160; If <m>A</m> and <m>B</m> are invertible <m>n \times n</m> matrices then <m>A + B</m> is also invertible.
            </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
            <p>
                False
            </p>
        </answer>
        <solution>
            <p>
                Solution text
            </p>
        </solution>
    </task>

    <task workspace="true">
        <statement>
            <p>
                <em>True &#160;  / &#160;  False</em>: &#160; If <m> A </m> is an <m> n \times n </m> matrix and <m>c</m> is a scalar such that <m>\det(A - cI_n) = 0</m>, then there exists a nonzero vector <m>\vec{v} \in \mathbb R ^n</m> such that <m>A \vec{v} \in \text{span}\{\vec{v} \}</m>
            </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
            <p>
                True.
            </p>
        </answer>
        <solution>
            <p>
                Solution text
            </p>
        </solution>
    </task>

    <task workspace="true">
        <statement>
            <p>
                <em>True &#160;  / &#160;  False</em>: &#160; If <m>A</m> and <m>B</m> are both <m>n \times n</m> matrices with pivots in each of their columns, then the product <m>AB</m> has a pivot in each of its columns
            </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
            <p>
                True
            </p>
        </answer>
        <solution>
            <p>
                Solution text
            </p>
        </solution>
    </task>
    
</problem>


</page>


<page>
<problem>
    <introduction>
        <p>
           (4 points) Indicate whether the following situations are possible or impossible. 
        </p>
    </introduction>

    <task workspace="0.5in">
        <statement>
            <p>
                <em>Possible &#160;  / &#160;  Impossible</em>: &#160; A <m>2 \times 2</m> matrix <m>A</m> with <m>\text{dim}(\Nul(A)) = 0</m> such that the system <m>A \vec{x} = \begin{bmatrix}1 \\ 2\end{bmatrix}</m> has no solution.
            </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
            <p>
                impossible.
            </p>
        </answer>
        <solution>
            <p>
                Solution Text
            </p>
        </solution>
    </task>

    <task workspace="0.5in">
        <statement>
            <p>
                <em>Possible &#160;  / &#160;  Impossible</em>: &#160; A <m>3 \times 5</m> matrix <m>A</m> so that <m>\rank(A) = 4</m>
            </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
            <p>
                impossible.
            </p>
        </answer>
        <solution>
            <p>
                Solution Text
            </p>
        </solution>
    </task>

    <task workspace="0.5in">
        <statement>
            <p>
                <em>Possible &#160;  / &#160;  Impossible</em>: &#160; Two <m>2 \times 2</m> non-zero matrices A and B, neither of which is <m>I_2</m>, with <m>AB = BA</m>
            </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
            <p>
                Possible.
            </p>
        </answer>
        <solution>
            <p>
                Solution Text
            </p>
        </solution>
    </task>

    <task workspace="0.5in">
        <statement>
            <p>
                <em>Possible &#160;  / &#160;  Impossible</em>: &#160; A <m>2 \times 2</m> invertible matrix <m>A = \begin{bmatrix}a \amp b \\ c \amp d\end{bmatrix}</m> so that <m>\det (A) = \det\begin{pmatrix}a \amp b \\ 2a + c \amp 2b + d\end{pmatrix}</m>
            </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
            <p>
                Possible.
            </p>
        </answer>
        <solution>
            <p>
                Solution Text. 
            </p>
        </solution>
    </task>


</problem>

<p workspace="0.5in">
    
</p>

<problem workspace="3in">
    <statement>
        <p>        
            (2 points) Let <m>A</m> be an <m>n \times n</m> matrix such that for every <m>\vec{b} \in \mathbb R ^n</m>, the system <m>A \vec{x} = \vec{b}</m> has a unique solution. Which of the following statements is FALSE?

            <m>\textit{Select only one}</m>
        </p>
        
        <ol marker="(a)">
            <li>The rows of <m>A</m> form a basis for <m>\mathbb R ^n</m></li>
            <li>dim <m>\{ \vec{x} | A \vec{x} = \vec{0} \} > 0</m>.</li>
            <li>The system <m>A^T \vec{x} = \vec{b}</m> has a unique solution for every <m>\vec{b} \in \mathbb R^n</m></li>
            <li>The columns of <m>A</m> are linearly independent.</li>
        </ol>

    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
            Option (b) is correct
        </p>
    </answer>
    <solution>
        <p>
            Option (a) is incorrect.
        </p>
        <p>
            Option (b) is correct.
        </p>
        <p>
            Option (c) is incorrect.
        </p>
        <p>
            Option (d) is incorrect.
        </p>
    </solution>
</problem>
    
</page>

<page>
    <problem workspace="3in">
    <statement>
        <p>        
            (2 points) Which of the following subsets of <m>\mathbb R ^3</m> are subspaces?

            <m>\textit{Select all that apply}</m>
        </p>
        
        <ol marker="(a)">
            <li><m>S_1 = \{ (x,y,z) \in \mathbb R^3 : x-2y+z = 1 \}</m></li>
            <li><m>S_2 = \{ s(1,0,1) + t(0,1,1) : s,t \in \mathbb R \}</m></li>
            <li><m>S_3 = \{ (x,y,z) \in \mathbb R^3 : xy=0 \}</m></li>
            <li><m>S_4 = \{ (x,y,z) \in \mathbb R^3 : x-2y+z = 0 \}</m></li>
        </ol>

    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
            Options (b) and (d) are correct
        </p>
    </answer>
    <solution>
        <p>
            Option (a) is incorrect.
        </p>
        <p>
            Option (b) is correct.
        </p>
        <p>
            Option (c) is incorrect.
        </p>
        <p>
            Option (d) is correct.
        </p>
    </solution>
</problem>



    <problem workspace="true">
        <statement>
            <p>
                (3 points) Suppose that <m>\det \begin{pmatrix} a \amp b \\ c \amp d \end{pmatrix} = 2 </m> and <m>\det \begin{pmatrix} a \amp b \\ e \amp f \end{pmatrix} = 5</m> and <m>\det \begin{pmatrix} c \amp d \\ e \amp f \end{pmatrix} = -2</m>. Find the value of the determinant below:
                <md>
                    \det \begin{pmatrix} a \amp 2 \amp b \\ c \amp 0 \amp d \\ e \amp 4 \amp f \end{pmatrix} = \framebox{$\phantom{$\begin{bmatrix} a \amp a \amp a  \\ b  \end{bmatrix}$}$ }
                </md>

            </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
            <p>
                <md>
                    \det \begin{pmatrix} a \amp 2 \amp b \\ c \amp 0 \amp d \\ e \amp 4 \amp f \end{pmatrix} = -4
                </md>
            </p>
        </answer>
        <solution>
            <p>
                Solution text 
            </p>
        </solution>
    </problem>
</page>

<page>
    <problem workspace="true">
        <statement>
            <p>    
                (3 points) Compute the area of the parallelogram <m>\mathcal{S}</m> having vertices <m>(-1,1), (0,4), (1,-4), \text{ and } (2,-1)</m>. Then, let <m>T : \mathbb R^2 \to \mathbb R^2</m> be the transformation with standard matrix <m>\begin{pmatrix}3 \amp 2 \\ 5 \amp 1 \end{pmatrix}</m>. Find the area of <m>T(\mathcal{S})</m>
                <md>
                    \text{Area}(\mathcal{S}) = \framebox{$\phantom{$\begin{bmatrix} a \amp a \amp a  \\ b  \end{bmatrix}$}$ }
                </md>
                <md>
                    \text{Area}(T(\mathcal{S})) = \framebox{$\phantom{$\begin{bmatrix} a \amp a \amp a  \\ b  \end{bmatrix}$}$ }
                </md>
                
            </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
            <p>
                <md>
                    \text{Area}(\mathcal{S}) = 11
                </md>
                <md>
                    \text{Area}((T\mathcal{S})) = 77
                </md>
            </p>
        </answer>
        <solution>
            <p>
                Solution text
            </p>
        </solution>
    </problem>

    <problem workspace="1.5in">
        <statement>
            <p>
                (4 points) Consider the system <m>A \vec{x} = \vec{b}</m>, where

                <md>
                    A = \begin{bmatrix} 7 \amp 4 \\ 3 \amp 2 \end{bmatrix} \text{ and } \vec{b} = \begin{bmatrix} 2 \\ 0 \end{bmatrix}
                </md>
                
                Let <m>A_1</m> and <m>A_2</m> be as in Cramer's Rule; that is, Let <m>A_i</m> be the matrix <m>A</m> with column <m>i</m> replaced with <m>\vec{b}</m>. Find <m>\det(A), \det(A_1), \det(A_2)</m>, and the solution vector <m>\vec{x}</m> 
            </p>
            <p>
                <md>
                    \det(A) = \framebox{$\phantom{$\begin{bmatrix} a \amp a \amp a  \\ b  \end{bmatrix}$}$ }
                </md>
                <md>
                    \det(A_1) = \framebox{$\phantom{$\begin{bmatrix} a \amp a \amp a  \\ b  \end{bmatrix}$}$ }
                </md>
                <md>
                    \det(A_2) = \framebox{$\phantom{$\begin{bmatrix} a \amp a \amp a  \\ b  \end{bmatrix}$}$ }
                </md>
                <md>
                    \vec{x} = \framebox{$\phantom{$\begin{bmatrix} a \amp a \amp a  \\ b \\ c \\ d \\ e  \end{bmatrix}$}$ }
                </md>
                
            </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
            <p>
                <md>
                    \det(A) = 2
                </md>
                <md>
                    \det(A_1) = 4
                </md>
                <md>
                    \det(A_2) = -6
                </md>
                <md>
                    \vec{x} = \begin{bmatrix} 2 \\ -3 \end{bmatrix}
                </md>
            </p>
        </answer>
        <solution>
            <p>
                Solution text 
            </p>
        </solution>
    </problem>
</page>

